Sure, here are some example sentences using the Serbian word "vic" (*joke*):

1. *Vic* je najbolji način da se opustimo i nasmejemo. (The *joke* is the best way to relax and laugh.)
2. Čuo sam novi *vic* sinoć, bio je baš smešan. (I heard a new *joke* last night, it was really funny.)
3. On stalno priča glupe *viceve*, nikad se ne nasmejem. (He always tells stupid *jokes*, I never laugh.)
4. Dobar *vic* može da razbije napetost u prostoriji. (A good *joke* can break the tension in the room.)
5. *Vic* nije uvek primeren u ozbiljnim situacijama. (A *joke* is not always appropriate in serious situations.)
6. Nisam siguran da sam razumeo taj *vic*, možeš li da mi ga objasniš? (I'm not sure I understood that *joke*, can you explain it to me?)
7. *Vicovi* koje on priča su uvek isti i već su dosadni. (The *jokes* he tells are always the same and they're already boring.)
8. Ne volim kad ljudi pričaju uvredljive *viceve*. (I don't like it when people tell offensive *jokes*.)
9. Sinoć smo do kasno noću pričali *viceve* i smejali se. (Last night we talked *jokes* and laughed until late at night.)
10. Nema ništa gore od neuspešnog *vica*, to može biti neprijatno. (There's nothing worse than an unsuccessful *joke*, it can be awkward.)